Lugari Member of Parliament Ayub Savula is currently being held at the Muthaiga Police Station after being arrested last night over alleged corruption, and conspiracy to defraud the government advertising agency  of more than 122 million shillings. Director of Prosecutions Noordin Haji, who directed the  arrest of the MP and 23 other people said he was satisfied with the evidence against him and former principal secretary in the State Department of Broadcasting and Telecommunications Sammy Itemere who approved the dealings.  